OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1772193824
OL,3,CCouncil to pay compensation to family
OL,4,Cover SEND education failures
OL,6,FFollowing a previous investigation by
OL,7,Fthe Local Government and Social Care
OL,8,FOmbudsman in August 2023, North
OL,9,FTyneside Council agreed to purchase
OL,10,Fspecialist technology allowing the
OL,11,Fchild to interact with their class
OL,12,Fwhile learning from home.
OL,14,FThe council said IT security
OL,15,Frestrictions and compatibility issues
OL,16,Fmeant the technology could not be
OL,17,Fprovided, but it then failed to
OL,18,Farrange any alternative education for
OL,19,F13 months.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1772193824
OL,3,CCouncil to pay compensation to family
OL,4,Cover SEND education failures
OL,6,FThe ombudsman's report has found the
OL,7,Fcouncil also did not attempt to put
OL,8,Fany other arrangements in place for
OL,9,Fthe child's education until September
OL,10,F2024. And then, it relied on the
OL,11,Fschool to make a referral to an
OL,12,Falternative provider, chasing the
OL,13,Fschool nine times rather than
OL,14,Farranging provision directly.
OL,16,FNow, following a further investigation
OL,17,Fby the ombudsman, North Tyneside
OL,18,FCouncil has apologised and agreed to
OL,19,Fpay to the family and pay them #5,900
OL,20,Fin recognition of the impact on the
OL,21,Fchild's education.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1772193824
OL,3,CCouncil to pay compensation to family
OL,4,Cover SEND education failures
OL,6,FITV News Tyne Tees has spoken to the
OL,7,Fmother of the child, who wanted to
OL,8,Fremain anonymous, she's described the
OL,9,Flast few years as an "horrific
OL,10,Fsituation".
OL,12,FShe went on to say: "You want your
OL,13,Fchild to be well, and he wasn't well
OL,14,Fbecause he was under a lot of stress
OL,15,Fbecause he's constantly being told
OL,16,F'you need to get into school', but
OL,17,Fthere was no way to support him to do
OL,18,Fthat."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1772193824
OL,3,CCouncil to pay compensation to family
OL,4,Cover SEND education failures
OL,6,F"It makes me really, really sad that
OL,7,Fhe wants to go onto sixth form, and
OL,8,Facademically absolutely is capable of
OL,9,Fthat. He's just not going to get the
OL,10,Fgrades that he's capable of, because
OL,11,Fhe's just missed so much."
OL,13,FAmderdeep Clarke, Local Government and
OL,14,FSocial Care Ombudsman, has said the
OL,15,Ffailure to provide the promised
OL,16,Ftechnology can only have had a can
OL,17,Fonly have had a "significant and
OL,18,Fdetrimental impact on the child's
OL,19,Feducation and wellbeing".
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1772193824
OL,3,CCouncil to pay compensation to family
OL,4,Cover SEND education failures
OL,6,FShe added: "North Tyneside Council
OL,7,Fallowed this case to drift without any
OL,8,Fmeaningful progress, and I am
OL,9,Fconcerned there appeared to have been
OL,10,Fno oversight or urgency to ensure this
OL,11,Fyoung person received the education
OL,12,Fthey were entitled to, especially
OL,13,Fgiven the council's previous agreement.
OL,15,F"I now hope the change it has
OL,16,Fcommitted to make to its management of
OL,17,Falternative provision does in fact
OL,18,Ftake place and will ensure greater
OL,19,Foversight in future of services for
OL,20,Fchildren who cannot attend school."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
